title: Aimi Kunitake
text:
is a Japanese <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player. She plays for <a href="Mynavi%20Sendai%20Ladies">Mynavi Sendai</a> and <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a>.
Club career.
Kunitake was born in <a href="Yamato%2C%20Kumamoto">Yamato, Kumamoto</a> on January 10, 1997. After graduating from <a href="Musashigaoka%20College">Musashigaoka College</a>, she joined <a href="L.League">L.League</a> club <a href="Nojima%20Stella%20Kanagawa%20Sagamihara">Nojima Stella Kanagawa Sagamihara</a> in 2017. She became a regular player as center back and played all 18 matches in first season.
National team career.
On July 29, 2018, Kunitake debuted for <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a> against <a href="Brazil%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Brazil</a>. She played 3 games for Japan in 2018.
